WEBVTT

00:04.070 --> 00:05.367
COME ON, BOYS.
SIT UP, SIT UP.

00:05.400 --> 00:06.435
COME ON, NAPKINS IN LAP.

00:06.470 --> 00:08.631
NOW, LISTEN, WE DON'T GET
TO GO OUT VERY OFI'EN,

00:08.670 --> 00:10.433
SO I WANT YOU
TO ORDER SOMETHING SPECIAL.

00:10.470 --> 00:12.574
HARBOR GRILL IS ONE
OF THE NICEST RESTAURANTS

00:12.610 --> 00:13.577
IN SANTA BARBARA.

00:13.610 --> 00:16.147
I'M GONNA HAVE NACHOS.

00:16.180 --> 00:18.341
NO WAY.

00:18.380 --> 00:20.644
DAD, I THINK
THAT GUY OVER THERE IS A SPY.

00:20.680 --> 00:22.409
AND HE'S TRYING TO POISON HER!

00:32.660 --> 00:35.220
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO SAY THIS,
SO I'M JUST GONNA SAY IT.

00:35.260 --> 00:38.798
MEGAN, WILL YOU MARRY ME?

00:38.830 --> 00:41.060
Y-YES.

00:41.100 --> 00:43.261
OF COURSE, YES!

00:43.310 --> 00:45.266
[applause]

00:45.310 --> 00:46.436
OH, COME ON, GUYS,

00:46.480 --> 00:48.607
YOU'VE SEEN
PEOPLE PROPOSE BEFORE.

00:48.640 --> 00:51.245
IT'S A VERY SPECIAL MOMENT.
ESPECIALLY FOR A MAN.

00:51.280 --> 00:52.816
YOU FALL IN LOVE
WITH A WOMAN.

00:52.850 --> 00:55.171
YOU DECIDE YOU'RE GONNA SPEND
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE WITH HER.

00:55.220 --> 00:57.211
REST OF MY LIFE
WITH A GIRL?

00:57.250 --> 00:58.342
NO WAY!

00:58.390 --> 01:00.210
I'M NEVER EVER
GONNA GET MARRIED!

01:00.260 --> 01:01.454
UGH.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.398
BY THE WAY,

01:06.430 --> 01:08.057
THEY'RE NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

01:12.170 --> 01:14.764
[yells]

01:14.800 --> 01:17.803
DO I NEED TO SET THIS
ON SLOW PITCH?

01:17.840 --> 01:19.501
HEY.

01:19.540 --> 01:21.098
I SWORE I SAW
THAT GUY EARLIER.

01:21.140 --> 01:22.846
OH, YEAH, YEAH.
HE'S BEEN FOLLOWING US ALL DAY.

01:22.880 --> 01:25.678
I'D SAY WORST P.I. EVER.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.075
CHECK THIS OUT.

01:34.720 --> 01:36.153
WHAT THE--NO, HE FOLLOWED ME
INTO THE BATHROOM?

01:36.190 --> 01:37.384
THAT'S MY SANCTUARY.

01:37.430 --> 01:38.283
I KNOW.

01:38.330 --> 01:40.719
ALL RIGHT, WE GO'ITA FIND OUT
WHAT HE WANTS.

01:40.760 --> 01:43.627
AND WE HAVE TO DO IT IN A WAY
THAT'S COOL AND CLEVER.

01:43.670 --> 01:44.694
I GOT IT.

01:52.310 --> 01:54.130
GYRO BALL!
(man)
HEY, WATCH IT!

01:54.180 --> 01:55.807
LET ME SHOW YOU
HOW IT'S DONE.

01:55.840 --> 01:57.102
WATCH OUT.

02:00.820 --> 02:02.811
[sighs]

02:07.820 --> 02:08.752
THAT VERY WELL MAY BE

02:08.790 --> 02:13.659
THE MOST HUMILIATING MOMENT
OF YOUR LIFE.

02:13.700 --> 02:15.656
I PITCH BETTER
FROM THE STRETCH.

02:19.640 --> 02:24.566
(Mace)
THAT'S ENOUGH.

02:24.610 --> 02:25.668
HEY.

02:25.710 --> 02:27.473
OW.

02:27.510 --> 02:28.499
AND THAT WAS FOR FOLLOWING ME

02:28.540 --> 02:29.802
INTO THE BATH ROOM.

02:29.850 --> 02:31.477
OKAY, SO YOU FIGURED OUT
I WAS FOLLOWING YOU.

02:31.510 --> 02:33.774
MY NAME IS MACE RHODEN.
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

02:33.820 --> 02:36.482
IF, UH, I MIGHT GIVE YOU
A LITTLE CRITICISM,

02:36.520 --> 02:38.784
I DON'T THINK YOU'VE
QUITE MASTERED THE PRIVATE PART.

02:38.820 --> 02:39.912
[Gus scoffs]

02:39.960 --> 02:41.382
OF COURSE, IF YOU'RE GOING

02:41.420 --> 02:42.785
FOR MOST OBVIOUS DETECTIVE...
NAILED IT.

02:42.830 --> 02:44.183
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM US?

02:44.230 --> 02:46.653
I WAS HIRED TO FIND YOU...
BY YOUR WIFE.

02:46.700 --> 02:48.224
[laughs]

02:48.260 --> 02:49.864
ONE MORE TINY PIECE
OF CRITICISM.

02:49.900 --> 02:52.733
YOU HAVEN'T MASTERED
THE INVESTIGATIVE PART EITHER.

02:52.770 --> 02:53.930
NEITHER OF US ARE MARRIED.

02:53.970 --> 02:56.302
UH, SHAWN, CAN I TALK
TO YOU FOR A MINUTE?

02:56.340 --> 02:58.262
[laughs]

02:58.310 --> 02:59.470
THIS GUY!

02:59.510 --> 03:01.603
TALKIN' ABOUT ONE OF US
BEING MARRIED.

03:01.640 --> 03:04.609
CAN YOU EVEN IMAGINE THAT?

03:04.650 --> 03:05.947
WHY AREN'T YOU LAUGHING?

03:08.650 --> 03:10.186
WHY AREN'T YOU LAUGHING?

03:12.660 --> 03:13.888
OH, MY GOD!

03:13.920 --> 03:17.424
YOU WERE MARRIED?

03:17.460 --> 03:21.396
[The Friendly Indians'
I Know You Know]

03:21.430 --> 03:22.920
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

03:22.970 --> 03:24.426
* THAT I'M NOT TELLING
THE TRUTH *

03:24.470 --> 03:25.994
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

03:26.030 --> 03:27.895
* THEY JUST DON'T HAVE
ANY PROOF *

03:27.940 --> 03:29.908
* EMBRACE THE DECEPTION

03:29.940 --> 03:31.407
* LEARN HOW TO BEND

03:31.440 --> 03:32.998
* YOUR WORST INHIBITIONS

03:33.040 --> 03:35.508
* TEND TO PSYCH YOU OUT
IN THE END *

03:35.540 --> 03:38.475
* I KNOW YOU KNOW *

03:41.650 --> 03:42.639
(Shawn)
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU WERE MARRIED!

03:42.690 --> 03:45.386
BACHELOR PARTY IS TAINTED.

03:45.420 --> 03:46.557
I DIDN'T GET TO GIVE
MY BRILLIANT SPEECH

03:46.590 --> 03:48.581
THAT I'VE BEEN PLANNING
SINCE WE WERE SEVENTH GRADERS.

03:48.620 --> 03:50.781
YOU HAVE NOT.

03:50.830 --> 03:53.492
YOU HAVE A BOOK OF SPEECHES?

03:53.530 --> 03:55.498
I WROTE THOSE A LONG TIME AGO.

03:55.530 --> 03:58.294
YOU ALREADY WROTE MY EULOGY?

03:58.330 --> 03:59.536
I DON'T REMEMBER THAT.

03:59.570 --> 04:00.537
"GUS IS SURVIVED

04:00.570 --> 04:04.006
BY HIS BEST FRIEND SHAWN SPENCER
AND 12 CATS."

04:04.040 --> 04:06.031
LOOK, THE SPEECHES
ARE NOT THE POINT, GUS.

04:06.070 --> 04:08.732
THE POINT IS, WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME YOU WERE MARRIED?

04:08.780 --> 04:11.806
I DIDN'T TELL ANYONE.
I WAS EMBARRASSED.

04:11.850 --> 04:13.943
LOOK, I'M SORRY.
I WAS WRONG FOR NOT TELLING YOU.

04:13.980 --> 04:16.346
BUT, DUDE, YOU KNOW
WHEN I GET MARRIED FOR REAL

04:16.390 --> 04:17.743
YOU'LL BE STANDING UP THERE
ON THAT ALTAR,

04:17.790 --> 04:19.985
RIGHT NEXT TO ME,
AS MY BEST MAN.

04:20.020 --> 04:22.818
THANK YOU FOR SAYING THAT.

04:22.860 --> 04:23.827
I NEEDED TO HEAR IT.

04:23.860 --> 04:24.827
YOU'RE WELCOME.

04:24.860 --> 04:26.999
SO WHO IS THIS HARLOT?

04:27.030 --> 04:29.999
IT WAS SPRING BREAK '97.

04:30.030 --> 04:32.021
I WAS IN MAZATLAN
WITH SOME COLLEGE FRIENDS.

04:32.070 --> 04:34.538
'97?

04:34.570 --> 04:36.709
TELL ME YOU WEREN'T STILL
ROCKIN' THE SWEATER VEST.

04:36.740 --> 04:39.777
WHAT? NO.

04:39.810 --> 04:41.835
HER NAME WAS MIRA GAFFNEY.

04:41.880 --> 04:46.317
I'LL NEVER FORGET
THE FIRST TIME I SAW HER.

04:46.350 --> 04:49.319
['90s club music]

04:49.350 --> 04:50.317
*

04:50.350 --> 04:52.614
[loud heartbeat]

05:04.400 --> 05:06.493
(Gus)
MIRA WAS LIKE
NO OTHER GIRL I EVER DATED.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.997
SHE COULD GET ME TO DO THINGS
NO ONE ELSE COULD EVER DO.

05:09.040 --> 05:13.830
SO SERIOUSLY?
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN SKYDIVING?

05:13.880 --> 05:16.474
WELL, I REALLY
DON'T LIKE PLANES.

05:16.510 --> 05:18.102
OR HEIGHTS.
OR JUMPSUITS.

05:18.150 --> 05:19.105
[laughter]

05:19.150 --> 05:21.846
NO, YOU LIKE
SWEATER VESTS.

05:21.880 --> 05:23.108
I DO.

05:23.150 --> 05:25.710
SO YOU'RE
A SKYDIVING VIRGIN?

05:25.750 --> 05:27.957
YEAH !

05:27.990 --> 05:29.423
I'M GONNA TAKE YOU!
WE'LL GO!

05:29.460 --> 05:30.484
IT'S AMAZING!
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT!

05:30.530 --> 05:31.554
OKAY.

05:31.590 --> 05:32.852
(Shawn)
DUDE, SKYDIVING'S ONE THING,

05:32.900 --> 05:34.595
BUT HOW DID SHE GET YOU
TO MARRY HER?

05:34.630 --> 05:37.758
(Gus)
TH REE WORDS.
THREE LITTLE WORDS.

05:37.800 --> 05:40.462
LET'S TRY GOLDSCHLAGER!

05:40.500 --> 05:41.660
(Gus)
AND FOUR HOURS LATER...

05:41.700 --> 05:44.669
[upbeat Latin music]

05:44.710 --> 05:47.076
*

05:47.110 --> 05:48.702
(Shawn)
OH, MY GOD.

05:48.740 --> 05:50.708
AND YOUR BEST MAN
WAS A GOAT?

05:50.750 --> 05:53.548
I WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE THAT GOAT!

05:53.580 --> 05:55.719
SHAWN, WE'RE ON ME NOW.

05:55.750 --> 05:58.480
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M--I'M SORRY.

05:58.520 --> 06:00.454
MAN, I HAVEN'T THOUGHT

06:00.490 --> 06:01.616
ABOUT HER IN SO LONG.

06:01.660 --> 06:03.651
PEOPLE USED
TO CALL HER HURRICANE MIRA

06:03.690 --> 06:06.591
BECAUSE SHE WAS THIS WILD,
BEAUTIFUL, INSANE GIRL.

06:06.630 --> 06:08.029
SO WHO BROKE IT OFF?

06:08.060 --> 06:11.393
ME.
AND IT GOT WEIRD REAL QUICK.

06:11.430 --> 06:13.159
SHE CALLED ME, LIKE, 100 TIMES
IN ONE DAY.

06:13.200 --> 06:15.737
AND THREATENED
TO BURN DOWN MY APARTMENT.

06:15.770 --> 06:17.738
MIRA REALLY HAS
A THING FOR FIRE, HUH?

06:17.770 --> 06:19.829
BUT THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT HER.
IT JUST STUCK WITH ME.

06:19.880 --> 06:22.030
I HAVE NEVER FELT THAT WAY
ABOUT ANY OTHER WOMAN.

06:22.080 --> 06:24.002
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S IT.
I NEED TO MEET THIS TROLLOP.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.005
YOU WANNA COME WITH ME?

06:25.050 --> 06:26.677
[scoffing]
YEAH !

06:26.720 --> 06:29.484
YOU BET--BUT, DUDE, LISTEN,
I DON'T KNOW

06:29.520 --> 06:30.919
IF I CAN CONTROL MYSELF
AROUND HER,

06:30.950 --> 06:32.679
SO YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
THAT YOU'LL STOP ME

06:32.720 --> 06:34.608
FROM BEING SUCKED
INTO HURRICANE MIRA AGAIN.

06:34.660 --> 06:37.026
JUST CALL ME
THE SUCK-STOPPER.

06:37.060 --> 06:38.550
SCRATCH THAT.

06:38.590 --> 06:40.023
DON'T--DON'T EVER
CALL ME THAT.

06:40.060 --> 06:42.927
I WONDER WHY SHE WANTS
TO SEE ME.

06:42.970 --> 06:44.699
I DON'T KNOW.

06:44.730 --> 06:47.392
MAYBE SHE WANTS TO INTRODUCE YOU
TO LITI'LE GUS JUNIOR.

06:49.140 --> 06:50.937
OR NOT.

06:56.180 --> 06:57.442
(Lassiter)
HOLD IT!

06:57.480 --> 06:58.742
S.B.P.D.!

06:59.010 --> 07:00.716
I SAID STOP!

07:00.750 --> 07:01.819
HOLD IT!

07:01.850 --> 07:03.886
LOOK OUT!

07:03.920 --> 07:04.887
[grunts]

07:04.920 --> 07:05.887
SON OF A...

07:05.920 --> 07:08.912
[sighs]

07:10.260 --> 07:12.797
I SAID FREEZE, YOU--
S.B.P.D.!

07:16.800 --> 07:17.562
[grunts]

07:17.600 --> 07:19.693
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN SILENT.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.059
O'HARA,
H-HOW DID YOU JUST--

07:21.100 --> 07:23.102
JUST HAD A HUNCH
HE LIVED IN THE AREA.

07:23.140 --> 07:25.028
I FIGURED HE'D TRY TO LOSE US
BY HOPPING ONE OF THE FENCES

07:25.070 --> 07:26.799
BETWEEN HOPE STREET
AND THE 101.

07:26.840 --> 07:28.876
LET'S GO.

07:32.050 --> 07:33.119
I'M IMPRESSED.

07:33.150 --> 07:35.038
SHUT UP.

07:35.080 --> 07:37.810
(Lassiter)
COME ON, O'HARA, LEVEL WITH ME.

07:37.850 --> 07:39.579
THAT WAS REALLY JUST A HUNCH?

07:39.620 --> 07:41.611
YES, FOR THE TENTH TIME.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.127
DID HE, LIKE, DROP HIS WALLET
OR A PIECE OF MAIL

07:43.160 --> 07:44.229
WITH HIS ADDRESS ON IT?

07:44.260 --> 07:46.125
HAVE YOU BEEN
TO HIS HOUSE BEFORE?

07:46.160 --> 07:47.957
WHY WOULD I HAVE BEEN
TO HIS HOUSE?

07:48.000 --> 07:49.661
I DON'T KNOW.
YOU DATE.

07:49.700 --> 07:52.567
I JUST HAPPEN TO BE GOOD
AT DEDUCT IVE REASONING.

07:52.600 --> 07:54.534
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN STUDYING
FOR THE DETECTIVE'S EXAM,

07:54.570 --> 07:56.538
AND THE DEDUCTIVE REASONING PART
IS JUST KILLING ME.

07:56.570 --> 07:58.162
MAYBE YOU COULD TUTOR ME
SOME TIME?

07:58.210 --> 07:59.609
SURE. OKAY.

07:59.640 --> 08:00.868
WELL, YOU KNOW,
IF ANYONE'S GONNA TUTOR YOU,

08:00.910 --> 08:01.774
IT SHOULD BE ME.

08:01.810 --> 08:03.641
AFI'ER ALL, I DO HOLD
THE DEPARTMENT RECORD

08:03.680 --> 08:05.739
FOR THE HIGHEST SCORE
ON THE DETECTIVE'S EXAM.

08:05.780 --> 08:08.840
97.2.

08:10.250 --> 08:12.115
WHAT?

08:14.660 --> 08:17.879
I HAVE TO GO WASH OUT
THE, UH, DRUNK TANK.

08:17.930 --> 08:18.749
YEAH !

08:21.630 --> 08:24.793
WHAT, DID SOMEONE BEAT
MY SCORE?

08:24.830 --> 08:25.762
OH, HEY.
I HEARD ABOUT THE COLLAR.

08:25.800 --> 08:26.789
NICE WORK.
ANOTHER CASE CLOSED.

08:26.840 --> 08:28.569
(Lassiter)
CHIEF.
YEAH?

08:28.600 --> 08:30.761
DID SOMEONE SCORE HIGHER THAN ME
ON THE DETECTIVE'S EXAM?

08:30.810 --> 08:33.734
I BELIEVE
O'HARA DID.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.270
O'HARA?

08:35.310 --> 08:36.868
HMM?

08:36.910 --> 08:38.047
YOU BEAT MY SCORE?

08:38.080 --> 08:40.310
ONLY BY A LITTLE.

08:40.350 --> 08:41.715
HOW MUCH?

08:41.750 --> 08:43.149
98.4.

08:43.190 --> 08:44.339
[whistles]

08:44.390 --> 08:46.858
GOSH, YOU KNOW, I CHECK ALL
THOSE SCORES EVERY THREE MONTHS.

08:46.890 --> 08:48.551
HOW COME I DIDN'T KNOW
ABOUT THIS?

08:48.590 --> 08:50.751
WELL, BECAUSE I MADE DETECTIVE
WHEN I WAS IN MIAMI.

08:50.790 --> 08:53.896
SO YOU WOULDN'T SEE
THOSE RESULTS.

08:53.930 --> 08:54.851
AND I DIDN'T WANNA TELL YOU

08:54.900 --> 08:57.027
BECAUSE I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU HATE TO LOSE.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.719
I DO NOT HATE TO LOSE.

08:58.770 --> 09:00.863
LOOK, WE BOTH DID WELL
ON THE EXAM.

09:00.900 --> 09:02.902
AND THOSE SCORES
DON'T MATTER TO ME.

09:02.940 --> 09:04.066
WHAT MATTERS TO ME

09:04.110 --> 09:05.805
IS THAT I RESPECT YOU

09:05.840 --> 09:07.899
AS A COP
AND AS A FRIEND,

09:07.940 --> 09:09.578
AND I REALLY, REALLY HOPE

09:09.610 --> 09:11.339
THIS DOESN'T BECOME A THING
BETWEEN US.

09:11.380 --> 09:14.611
THIS IS NOT GONNA BECOME
A THING BETWEEN US.

09:19.990 --> 09:22.754
(Shawn)
THAT MACE GUY SAID
THIS WAS THE PLACE TO MEET HER.

09:22.790 --> 09:23.859
MAYBE SHE WORKS HERE.

09:23.890 --> 09:25.027
(Gus)
THAT WOULDN'T SURPRISE ME.

09:25.060 --> 09:26.152
SHE'S HAD, LIKE,
A THOUSAND JOBS.

09:26.190 --> 09:27.896
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH THAT.

09:27.930 --> 09:31.058
AND SHE DOESN'T JUST WORK HERE.
THE WINE IS NAMED MIRA.

09:31.100 --> 09:33.694
MAYBE THEY NAME A WINE
AI-TER ALL THEIR EMPLOYEES.

09:33.740 --> 09:35.890
REMIND ME TO GRAB A BOTTLE
OF LEONARD ON THE WAY OUT.

09:35.940 --> 09:37.999
(Mira)
BURTON GUSTER?

09:40.910 --> 09:44.073
[heartbeat]

09:44.110 --> 09:46.305
(Shawn)
GUS.

09:46.350 --> 09:48.875
GUS.

09:48.920 --> 09:49.944
GUS!

09:49.990 --> 09:52.140
WHAT DO I SAY?
HOW'S MY BREATH?

09:52.190 --> 09:53.282
RELAX.
REMEMBER THE PLAN.

09:53.320 --> 09:54.810
WHAT PLAN?

09:54.860 --> 09:55.815
I FORGOT THE PLAN.

09:55.860 --> 09:57.987
[giggles excitedly]

10:00.400 --> 10:01.651
HOW ARE YOU?

10:01.700 --> 10:03.019
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU IN WHAT?
TEN YEARS?

10:03.070 --> 10:06.119
AND NOW LOOK, BOOM,
HERE YOU ARE.

10:06.170 --> 10:08.730
HI, I'M SHAWN.

10:08.770 --> 10:09.964
HI.

10:10.010 --> 10:12.638
I, UH, I GAVE HIM
A REALLY TOUGH RIDDLE

10:12.680 --> 10:13.476
ON THE WAY OVER,

10:13.510 --> 10:14.909
SO HE'S PROBABLY NOW
JUST FIGURING OUT

10:14.940 --> 10:17.841
THAT THE DOCTOR
WAS A WOMAN.

10:17.880 --> 10:18.847
[giggIeSJ
NO, NO.

10:18.880 --> 10:19.847
HE'S DONE THIS BEFORE.

10:19.880 --> 10:21.871
HE DID THIS
WHEN WE FIRST MET.

10:21.920 --> 10:22.989
I THINK IT'S KINDA CUTE
ACTUALLY.

10:23.020 --> 10:24.817
IF WE JUST KEEP TALKING,
HE'LL CATCH UP.

10:24.850 --> 10:27.717
SO I HEAR THAT YOU GUYS HAVE
A DETECTIVE AGENCY OR SOMETHING.

10:27.760 --> 10:28.852
MIRA!

10:28.890 --> 10:29.925
MIRA!

10:29.960 --> 10:31.154
UH, HI.

10:31.190 --> 10:33.158
HI THERE.
WELCOME.

10:33.200 --> 10:35.350
WOW.
YOU LOOK AMAZING.

10:35.400 --> 10:36.697
NO, YOU DO.

10:36.730 --> 10:37.992
NO, YOU REALLY
LOOK AMAZING.

10:38.030 --> 10:38.724
NO, YOU DO.

10:38.770 --> 10:40.795
A LITTLE BIT, BUT,
I MEAN, WOW!

10:40.840 --> 10:41.738
THE ONLY THING
THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN BETTER WAS

10:41.770 --> 10:42.862
IF YOU HAD WORN ONE
OF THOSE SWEATER VESTS.

10:42.910 --> 10:45.663
I LOVE IT--DO YOU STILL WEAR
THOSE SWEATER VESTS?

10:45.710 --> 10:46.836
[Gus laughing]

10:46.880 --> 10:48.973
GUS, I REMEMBER THE PLAN.
THIS ISN'T IT.

10:49.010 --> 10:50.841
OH, I KNOW.
LET'S CELEBRATE WITH A DRINK.

10:50.880 --> 10:52.074
OKAY?

10:52.110 --> 10:53.418
BUT NOT GOLDSCHLAGER, RIGHT?

10:53.450 --> 10:54.417
[laughs]

10:54.450 --> 10:55.439
I'M IN TROUBLE.

10:55.480 --> 10:56.811
ALL RIGHT, JUST BE COOL.

10:56.850 --> 10:58.784
AND MAKE YOUR ARM PITS
STOP SWEATING.

10:58.820 --> 11:02.722
OKAY, SO THIS IS OUR SANGIOVESE
FROM LAST YEAR.

11:02.760 --> 11:04.978
[laughter]

11:05.030 --> 11:06.054
GOLDSCHLAGER!

11:06.090 --> 11:07.455
[laughs]

11:07.500 --> 11:09.195
GUS.

11:09.230 --> 11:11.118
SO HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN WORKING HERE?

11:11.170 --> 11:13.764
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.
THIS IS MY FAMILY'S PLACE.

11:13.800 --> 11:14.994
WE HAVE
THREE WINERIES.

11:15.040 --> 11:16.268
THIS ONE,
A NEW ONE IN NAPA,

11:16.300 --> 11:17.938
AND THEN THERE'S THE ONE
IN SPAIN, WHICH OF COURSE

11:17.970 --> 11:20.279
I CAN'T GO TO BECAUSE I PUNCHED
THE BULL IN PAMPLONA.

11:20.310 --> 11:21.971
SO, MIRA, UH,

11:22.010 --> 11:24.478
WHAT MADE YOU WANNA SEE ME
AI-TER ALL THIS TIME?

11:24.510 --> 11:28.446
WELL, UM,
I KINDA HAVE SOME BIG NEWS.

11:28.480 --> 11:31.119
IS IT GUS JUNIOR?

11:31.150 --> 11:32.117
WHAT?

11:32.150 --> 11:34.311
NOTHING.

11:34.360 --> 11:35.952
I'M GETTING MARRIED.

11:35.990 --> 11:36.922
OH.

11:36.960 --> 11:38.757
OH.
YEAH, YEAH.

11:38.790 --> 11:41.156
HIS NAME IS JANN,
AND HE'S FROM SWEDEN.

11:41.200 --> 11:42.929
ALTHOUGH HE'S LIVED
ALL OVER THE WORLD.

11:42.970 --> 11:46.167
AND I MET HIM AT THIS WINE
CONVENTION A FEW MONTHS AGO.

11:46.200 --> 11:47.838
MIRA, THAT'S AWESOME.
CONGRATULATIONS.

11:47.870 --> 11:48.837
THAN KS.

11:48.870 --> 11:51.338
SO THE THING IS, GUS,

11:51.370 --> 11:54.100
THAT, UH, OUR WEDDING CHAPEL
IN MAZATLAN,

11:54.140 --> 11:56.005
THEY ACTUALLY SENT
THE MARRIAGE LICENSE

11:56.040 --> 11:57.405
TO THE U.S.,
SO THE ANNULMENT ISN'T OFFICIAL.

11:57.450 --> 11:58.439
SO I KINDA JUST NEED YOU

11:58.480 --> 11:59.469
TO FILL OUT SOME PAPERWORK.

11:59.510 --> 12:00.977
IS THAT COOL?

12:01.020 --> 12:02.112
YES.
OH, SURE.

12:02.150 --> 12:03.117
YES.
OKAY, SURE.

12:03.150 --> 12:04.048
OH, GOOD.
GOOD.

12:04.090 --> 12:07.457
I WAS A LITTLE WORRIED.

12:07.490 --> 12:08.752
SO WHEN IS THE BIG DAY?

12:08.790 --> 12:10.985
IT'S ACTUALLY TOMORROW.

12:11.030 --> 12:12.122
ON LEDBETTER BEACH.

12:12.160 --> 12:13.320
IT'S JUST GONNA BE
A SMALL THING.

12:13.360 --> 12:15.248
I KINDA WANTED IT TO BE HERE,
BUT HE WANTED AT A BEACH.

12:15.300 --> 12:16.449
I THOUGHT, IT'S REALLY THE ONLY
THING HE REALLY WANTS,

12:16.500 --> 12:18.058
SO I THINK I'LL LET HIM DO IT.

12:18.100 --> 12:20.193
IT'S KINDA ROMANTIC.
AND--OH, DAD!

12:20.240 --> 12:21.832
(David)
YEAH?

12:21.870 --> 12:24.236
DAD, THIS IS SHAWN.

12:24.270 --> 12:25.828
IT'S SHAWN, RIGHT?
YEAH, SHAWN.

12:25.870 --> 12:28.077
AND THIS IS GUS.

12:28.110 --> 12:30.499
AH, AH, YES, GUSTER.

12:30.550 --> 12:31.505
SO THIS IS THE YOUNG MAN
THAT TRICKED YOU

12:31.550 --> 12:33.177
INTO MARRYING HIM, HUH?
Y-YEAH.

12:33.220 --> 12:35.040
TYPICAL.

12:35.080 --> 12:36.377
MIRA, I NEED
TO SPEAK TO YOU.

12:36.420 --> 12:37.444
OKAY.
GENTLEM EN.

12:37.490 --> 12:39.481
ONLY THE FIRST GLASS IS FREE.

12:42.060 --> 12:43.254
OH, OH!

12:43.290 --> 12:44.257
WHY DON'T YOU COME
TO THE WEDDING?

12:44.290 --> 12:45.359
OH, MIRA.

12:45.390 --> 12:47.096
PLEASE, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE!

12:47.130 --> 12:51.066
COME, COME,
COME, COME, COME, COME!

12:51.100 --> 12:52.089
THAT'S VERY SWEET OF YOU,
BUT WE'RE A LITTLE TIGHT--

12:52.130 --> 12:54.098
WHAT TIME
SHOULD VG/ILEJSBE THERE?

12:54.140 --> 12:55.391
SHAWN,
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

12:55.440 --> 12:57.169
MIRA, OF COURSE
WE WILL COME.

12:57.210 --> 12:58.268
OKAY, GOOD.

12:58.310 --> 12:59.208
SO I'M GONNA GO GET

12:59.240 --> 13:00.935
THE WEDDING INFO
AND THE ANNULMENT PAPERS.

13:00.980 --> 13:03.448
OH, I HOPE I DON'T EVER SAY
THAT SENTENCE AGAIN.

13:03.480 --> 13:05.107
[Mira giggling]

13:05.150 --> 13:06.344
DUDE.

13:06.380 --> 13:08.848
SHE JUST SMELLED SO NICE.

13:08.880 --> 13:11.110
DON'T JUDGE ME, SHAWN.
I'M WEAK.

13:13.260 --> 13:15.012
(Gus)
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE LATE.

13:15.060 --> 13:17.119
LOOK, I'M NOT THE ONE THAT SPENT
TWO HOURS PICKING OUT

13:17.160 --> 13:19.082
THE PERFECT
SHIRT-TIE-EYES COMBO.

13:19.130 --> 13:20.199
FINALLY,

13:20.230 --> 13:22.050
WHAT THE HELL
AM I DOING HERE?

13:22.100 --> 13:24.068
SHAWN, YOU CANCELLED TWICE.
YOU'RE LATE.

13:24.100 --> 13:24.919
I'M HUNGRY.

13:24.970 --> 13:26.323
LOOK, WE'RE GONNA EAT LUNCH.
I PROMISE.

13:26.370 --> 13:28.099
THERE MAY EVEN BE
A GRILLED CHEESE BAR

13:28.140 --> 13:30.108
AND SOME DANCING INVOLVED.
WHAT, AT THE CRAB SHACK?

13:30.140 --> 13:31.209
CHANGE OF PLANS.
WE'RE GOING TO A WEDDING.

13:31.240 --> 13:33.470
I CAN'T GO TO A WEDDING.
I'M NOT DRESSED FOR A WEDDING.

13:33.510 --> 13:34.579
DAD, YOU LOOK SHARP AS A TACK.

13:34.610 --> 13:36.077
NO ONE WILL EVEN NOTICE.

13:36.110 --> 13:37.145
SHAWN.
SH--

13:41.450 --> 13:44.089
[excitedly]
HI! HI, HI, HI.

13:44.120 --> 13:45.610
HI.
HI.
I'M STACY.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.880
I'M MIRA'S FRIEND.

13:47.920 --> 13:49.979
IS HE WITH YOU?

13:50.030 --> 13:51.850
OH, YEAH, HE'S FINE.
I JUST WON HIM IN A BET.

13:51.890 --> 13:53.198
OH!

13:53.230 --> 13:55.198
[giggIeSJ
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

13:55.230 --> 13:57.198
YOU DO?
YOU'RE GUS.

13:57.230 --> 13:58.959
GUS!

13:59.000 --> 14:00.433
WE'VE BEEN WAITING
FOR YOU.

14:00.470 --> 14:02.461
MIRA SAID WE COULDN'T START
UNTIL YOU GOT HERE.

14:02.500 --> 14:04.365
AI-TER ALL, YOU ARE
A VERY SPECIAL GUEST.

14:04.410 --> 14:06.037
I AM?

14:06.070 --> 14:09.130
OH, DON'T BE NERVOUS, YOU.
YOU'LL DO GREAT.

14:09.180 --> 14:10.499
YOUR SPOT'S JUST RIGHT
UP FRONT THERE.

14:10.550 --> 14:12.347
LUCKY.
[glggleSJ

14:12.380 --> 14:13.517
NOW GET UP THERE!

14:13.550 --> 14:14.915
OKAY.

14:14.950 --> 14:16.315
LITTLE TIE.
OH!

14:16.350 --> 14:18.238
HE'S HERE!

14:21.260 --> 14:23.353
[string quartet begins playing]

14:23.390 --> 14:28.953
*

14:29.000 --> 14:31.321
OH, MY GOD.

14:31.370 --> 14:32.962
THIS IS MY WEDDING.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.297
GUS, THAT'S CRAZY.
NO, IT'S NOT.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.659
IT'S MIRA.

14:35.700 --> 14:38.464
IT'S JUST LIKE HER TO TRY
TO PULL SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

14:38.510 --> 14:39.465
YOU GOTTA GET ME
OUTTA HERE.

14:39.510 --> 14:41.478
OKAY, RELAX.

14:41.510 --> 14:43.239
I CAN HAVE YOU IN MEXICO
IN FOUR HOURS.

14:43.280 --> 14:44.372
BUT WE GOTTA DYE YOUR HAIR,
CHANGE YOUR NAME,

14:44.410 --> 14:45.900
CUT OFF YOUR FINGERTIPS
SO YOU CAN'T BE IDENTIFIED.

14:45.950 --> 14:48.168
I DON'T NEED FINGERTIPS.

14:48.220 --> 14:48.970
EXCUSE ME, EVERYONE.

14:49.020 --> 14:52.012
I'M AFRAID
WE HAVE HORRIBLE NEWS.

14:52.050 --> 14:54.280
IT SEEMS JANN IS MISSING.

14:54.320 --> 14:55.059
YES!
WHOO!

14:55.090 --> 14:56.978
(Gus)
OH, THAT WAS CLOSE!

14:57.030 --> 14:58.054
SWEET!

15:02.660 --> 15:05.128
[Mira sobbing]

15:05.170 --> 15:06.592
SWEETIE PIE.

15:06.630 --> 15:07.597
IT'S...

15:07.640 --> 15:09.596
NO, I DON'T WANT THE WATER.

15:09.640 --> 15:12.131
BABY, IT'S BEEN TWO HOURS.

15:12.170 --> 15:14.138
I DON'T THINK
HE'S COMING.

15:14.180 --> 15:14.976
OF COURSE
HE'S NOT COMING.

15:15.010 --> 15:16.432
HE DIDN'T SHOW UP WEDNESDAY
FOR GOLF,

15:16.480 --> 15:18.038
THURSDAY FOR THE BARBEQUE,

15:18.080 --> 15:18.978
YESTERDAY
FOR THE REHEARSAL DINNER.

15:19.010 --> 15:21.149
WHY WOULD HE SHOW UP
TO HIS OWN WEDDING?

15:21.180 --> 15:22.943
NO, DAD, YOU KNOW
THAT HE GOT CALLED TO WORK

15:22.990 --> 15:24.048
ON THOSE OTHER THINGS.

15:24.090 --> 15:26.046
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU TALKED ME INTO THIS.

15:26.090 --> 15:27.580
(Phyllis)
BABY, CAN WE AT LEAST LET
THE PEOPLE EAT SOMETHING?

15:27.620 --> 15:28.985
NO.

15:29.020 --> 15:32.126
NOBODY GETS TO EAT
UNTIL I'M MARRIED!

15:37.200 --> 15:39.168
THAT'S IT, SHAWN.
I'M OUTTA HERE.

15:39.200 --> 15:43.034
IT'S RUDE TO INVITE PEOPLE
TO AN EVENT AND NOT FEED 'EM.

15:43.070 --> 15:44.503
(Mira)
SOMEBODY FIX IT!

15:44.540 --> 15:47.134
LOOK AT HER IN THAT DRESS.

15:47.180 --> 15:48.238
SHE'S SO BEAUTIFUL.

15:48.280 --> 15:49.736
[crying]

15:49.780 --> 15:52.499
DUDE, I GOTTA GET YOU
OUTTA HERE.

15:52.550 --> 15:55.075
THIS MUST BE HOW SHE FELT
AFTER I ANNULLED OUR WEDDING.

15:55.120 --> 15:56.576
I FEEL SO BAD FOR HER.

15:56.620 --> 15:58.178
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
COME ON, LET'S HIT IT.

16:00.490 --> 16:01.457
WHAT?

16:01.490 --> 16:03.287
MIRA.
YEAH?

16:03.330 --> 16:05.150
I AM SO SORRY
TO HEAR ABOUT JANN.

16:05.190 --> 16:06.418
WE'LL HELP YOU FIND HIM.

16:06.460 --> 16:08.291
YOU WILL?
WE WILL?

16:08.330 --> 16:09.695
YES, WE DON'T HAVE ANY CASES
RIGHT NOW.

16:09.730 --> 16:11.061
WE'RE MORE
THAN HAPPY TO HELP.

16:11.100 --> 16:15.366
OH, GUSTER!
THANK YOU.

16:15.400 --> 16:17.402
JUST FINISHED MY CASE REPORTS
FOR THE WEEK,

16:17.440 --> 16:19.431
SPELL-CHECKED, COPIED,
AND COLLATED--TIME TO SPARE.

16:19.470 --> 16:21.335
MM.
GOOD FOR YOU.

16:21.380 --> 16:22.529
EXACTLY.

16:22.580 --> 16:23.569
O'HARA, I DO HOPE
YOU'RE NOT FALLING BEHIND

16:23.610 --> 16:24.679
ON YOUR PAPERWORK.

16:24.710 --> 16:27.417
THOSE REPORTS
LOOK GREAT, O'HARA.

16:27.450 --> 16:30.180
LISTEN, CAN YOU TRANSLATE
THESE FILES INTO SPANISH?

16:30.220 --> 16:31.744
NO PROBLEMA.

16:31.790 --> 16:33.109
YOU SPEAK SPANISH?

16:33.160 --> 16:35.549
IT'S A REQUIREMENT
IN MIAMI.

16:35.590 --> 16:37.387
WELL, THERE'S NOT THAT
VERY LARGE A LATINO POPULATION

16:37.430 --> 16:38.488
HERE IN SANTA BARBARA.

16:44.100 --> 16:45.658
MM!
UGH!

16:45.700 --> 16:47.691
THAT'S SO HOT!
MATT!

16:47.740 --> 16:49.196
DID YOU JUST BREW THIS?

16:53.510 --> 16:55.137
IT'S NOT TOO HOT FOR ME.

16:55.180 --> 16:57.205
PLEASE TELL ME YOU DIDN'T JUST
BURN YOUR MOUTH

16:57.250 --> 16:58.706
BECAUSE YOU'RE STILL PISSED
I SCORED HIGHER THAN YOU

16:58.750 --> 17:00.069
ON THAT STUPID EXAM?

17:00.120 --> 17:01.314
NO.

17:01.350 --> 17:02.817
UGH.

17:02.850 --> 17:04.078
HEY, DETECTIVE O'HARA!

17:04.120 --> 17:05.644
YOUR STOLEN REFRIGERATION TRUCK

17:05.690 --> 17:07.248
FROM THE SEAFOOD WAREHOUSE,

17:07.290 --> 17:08.814
THAT'S A 10-8-51, RIGHT?
YES.

17:08.860 --> 17:10.157
NO, HOLD ON.

17:10.190 --> 17:11.157
THAT TRUCK IS
A COMMERCIAL VEHICLE,

17:11.190 --> 17:13.226
SO TECH NICALLY
IT'S A 15-250.

17:13.260 --> 17:14.227
EXCUSE ME, DETECTIVE.

17:14.260 --> 17:16.421
HE WAS ASKING ME.

17:16.460 --> 17:17.688
NOW, IF THAT VEHICLE ENDS UP

17:17.730 --> 17:19.266
IN A CHOP SHOP,

17:19.300 --> 17:20.528
IT'S A 10-8-03.

17:20.570 --> 17:21.559
OF COURSE IF THERE'S
RECKLESS DRIVING INVOLVED,

17:21.600 --> 17:22.828
IT'S A 23-00-1.

17:22.870 --> 17:24.201
AND WATCH OUT
FOR THE ILLEGAL TRANSPORTATION

17:24.240 --> 17:25.207
OF HAZARDOUS MATERIALS.

17:25.240 --> 17:27.731
25-00-1.

17:27.780 --> 17:29.372
OKAY, THAT'S ENOUGH.

17:29.410 --> 17:32.174
I GOTTA GO GET
SOME PAPER ANYWAY.

17:32.210 --> 17:33.177
YOU KNOW WHAT?

17:33.220 --> 17:34.175
WHAT?

17:34.220 --> 17:35.710
I HAVE WORKED HARD.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.217
I HAVE DONE
EVERYTHING ASKED OF ME.

17:37.250 --> 17:38.342
I AM A GOOD COP,

17:38.390 --> 17:39.516
AND I'M NOT GOING
TO STAND HERE

17:39.550 --> 17:41.450
AND APOLOGIZE
FOR MY GOOD SCORE.

17:41.490 --> 17:43.287
SO YOU ARE JUST GONNA HAVE
TO GET OVER IT.

17:43.330 --> 17:44.285
YEAH.
I CAN'T DO THAT.

17:44.330 --> 17:45.456
WELL, THEN NOW WHAT?

17:45.490 --> 17:46.787
YOUR TRUCK.

17:46.830 --> 17:48.491
WHOEVER SOLVES THAT CASE
IS THE BETTER DETECTIVE.

17:48.530 --> 17:50.691
SOLVE YOUR OWN CASES.
IT'S A REFRIGERATION TRUCK.

17:50.730 --> 17:52.391
IT'S PRACTICALLY
A VICTIMLESS CRIME.

17:52.430 --> 17:54.398
WELL, I GUESS
YOU JUST DON'T COUNT THE PEOPLE

17:54.440 --> 17:55.532
WHO AREN'T GONNA GET
THEIR LOBSTER AND SAND DABS

17:55.570 --> 17:57.128
AS VICTIMS.

17:57.170 --> 17:58.467
I'M SURPRISED THE MIAMI P.D.
DIDN'T FAIL YOU

17:58.510 --> 18:00.671
FOR LACK OF COMPASSION.

18:00.710 --> 18:02.177
[groans]

18:02.210 --> 18:04.440
GUS, WHAT'S WRONG
WITH ME?

18:04.480 --> 18:08.849
WHAT IS IT THAT MAKES
ALL THE GUYS GO CRAZY ON ME?

18:08.880 --> 18:11.849
JANN WAS AN IDIOT
FOR GIVING YOU UP.

18:11.890 --> 18:13.653
YOU'RE SO SWEET.

18:13.690 --> 18:15.851
SWEET.

18:15.890 --> 18:19.849
SWEET GUS.

18:19.890 --> 18:21.824
YEAH, HE'S PRETTY SWEET
ALL RIGHT.

18:21.860 --> 18:24.795
HIS HEAD IS LIKE
A CHOCOLATE-COVERED HONEYDEW.

18:24.830 --> 18:27.731
NOW, WOULD ANYONE LIKE
TO TALK ABOUT "JAN?"

18:27.770 --> 18:29.362
(Gus)
IT'S JANN, WITH A "."J

18:29.400 --> 18:30.867
SHAWN IS RIGHT.
WE SHOULD DO THAT.

18:30.910 --> 18:34.676
SO THIS IS
ALL THAT I HAVE.

18:34.710 --> 18:37.474
I HAVE SOME PICTURES
OF US TOGETHER.

18:37.510 --> 18:39.171
AND A NOTE THAT HE WROTE ME.

18:39.210 --> 18:40.245
AND A LIPSTICK FROM HIM.

18:49.620 --> 18:51.588
DO YOU HAVE
ANY MORE PICTURES?

18:51.630 --> 18:53.325
NO.

18:56.930 --> 18:58.921
SHAWN.

18:58.970 --> 19:00.790
SHOULDN'T YOU MAYBE GO TALK
WITH MIRA'S PARENTS?

19:00.840 --> 19:01.829
I'LL FIND YOU
WHEN WE'RE FINISHED.

19:01.870 --> 19:02.837
I HAVEN'T FINISHED MY--

19:02.870 --> 19:04.269
IT'S FINE.
I'LL FINISH IT.

19:04.310 --> 19:07.302
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW TO WORK WITH CORK!

19:20.990 --> 19:21.957
MRS. GAFFNEY.

19:21.990 --> 19:23.821
HELLO.

19:23.860 --> 19:25.179
MY NAME IS SHAWN SPENCER.

19:25.230 --> 19:27.289
OH, I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

19:27.330 --> 19:30.299
YOU'RE THE PSYCHIC DETECTIVE
HELPING MIRA.

19:30.330 --> 19:31.968
YOU KNOW,

19:32.000 --> 19:34.639
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN FASCINATED
BY PEOPLE WITH "THE GIFT."

19:34.670 --> 19:35.830
UH, YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT THIS?

19:35.870 --> 19:36.837
WELL, THAT TAKES WORK.

19:36.870 --> 19:39.202
I'D LIKE TO ASK YOU
A QUESTION ABOUT "JAN."

19:39.240 --> 19:41.208
JANN?

19:41.240 --> 19:43.344
I WOULDN'T KNOW
THE FIRST THING ABOUT HIM.

19:43.380 --> 19:44.745
I SEE.

19:44.780 --> 19:46.668
BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T MET HIM?

19:46.710 --> 19:48.849
VERY GOOD.

19:48.880 --> 19:51.348
THIS IS OUR PRIVATE WINE

19:51.390 --> 19:52.948
AND ALCOHOL COLLECTION.

19:52.990 --> 19:54.355
OH, I SEE.

19:54.390 --> 19:55.209
I HAVE A PRIVATE ROOM

19:55.260 --> 19:56.955
FOR ALL
OF MY HELLO KITTY SHOT GLASSES

19:56.990 --> 19:58.389
AND WILD ANIMAL SCAT.

19:58.430 --> 20:00.421
I HAVE MANY INTERESTS.

20:00.460 --> 20:03.588
WELL, ONLY A PRIVILEGED FEW
ARE ALLOWED DOWN HERE.

20:03.630 --> 20:05.928
THE WINE IN THIS ROOM
IS WORTH OVER $1 MILLION.

20:05.970 --> 20:06.994
WE'VE BEEN COLLECTING IT

20:07.030 --> 20:08.634
FOR YEARS
FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD.

20:08.670 --> 20:11.002
WOULD YOU LIKE A GLASS?

20:11.040 --> 20:13.929
ACTUALLY, I PREFER
MY WINE IN A BOX.

20:13.980 --> 20:16.437
[laughs]

20:16.480 --> 20:17.572
WOW.

20:22.280 --> 20:23.281
I'VE OI-TEN HEARD

20:23.320 --> 20:24.446
THAT'S THE BEST WAY
TO SAVOR WINE.

20:24.490 --> 20:27.687
JUST SKIP OVER THE TASTE BUDS
AND GO RIGHT TO THE GULLET.

20:27.720 --> 20:30.359
I SWEAR, IF I HAVE TO DEAL
WITH ANOTHER TOURIST TODAY,

20:30.390 --> 20:31.857
MY HEAD IS GOING TO EXPLODE.

20:31.890 --> 20:33.426
AND DAVID DOESN'T LIKE
ME DRINKING

20:33.460 --> 20:34.620
IN FRONT OF THE GUESTS.

20:34.660 --> 20:37.299
SO, UH, HOW DID YOU MANAGE

20:37.330 --> 20:38.866
TO NEVER MEET JAN?

20:38.900 --> 20:40.993
WE TRIED TO.
SEVERAL TIMES.

20:41.040 --> 20:45.306
TAKE A SIP
BEFORE I FINISH THE BOTTLE.

20:45.340 --> 20:48.400
THAT'S--
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

20:48.440 --> 20:50.476
THAT'S A $30,000 BOTTLE
OF SPANISH SHERRY.

20:57.520 --> 20:58.987
MM.

20:59.020 --> 20:59.987
IT'S GOOD.

21:00.020 --> 21:02.386
YOU KNOW, SHAWN,

21:02.420 --> 21:07.448
I HAVE VERY FINE TASTE,
AND I LIKE MY WINE

21:07.500 --> 21:10.492
LIKE I LIKE MY MEN...

21:10.530 --> 21:14.398
WHITE AND HAIRY.

21:14.440 --> 21:15.839
THAT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE.

21:15.870 --> 21:17.838
NONE WHATSOEVER.

21:17.870 --> 21:20.634
BUT I CAN SEE
WHERE MIRA GETS HER SPUNKINESS.

21:20.680 --> 21:22.079
[laughter]

21:22.110 --> 21:23.304
PHYLLIS,

21:23.350 --> 21:24.772
SOME OF OUR GUESTS ARE GONNA--

21:24.810 --> 21:26.698
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

21:26.750 --> 21:28.047
I WAS JUST EXPLAINING
OUR FRUSTRATION

21:28.080 --> 21:29.445
OVER NEVER MEETING JANN.

21:29.480 --> 21:31.516
OH.
YEAH, THAT GUY.

21:31.550 --> 21:33.882
YEAH, EVERY TIME WE MADE PLANS,

21:33.920 --> 21:35.080
HE WOULD CHANGE THEM
AT THE LAST SECOND

21:35.120 --> 21:38.624
WITH THAT SAME LAME EXCUSE
ABOUT HAVING TO WORK OVERSEAS.

21:38.660 --> 21:41.959
I CANNOT BELIEVE
THAT I SHUT DOWN MY WINERY

21:42.000 --> 21:43.968
FOR THIS WEDDING.

21:44.000 --> 21:45.467
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN BETTER.

21:48.440 --> 21:52.536
MIRA'S CHOICES IN MEN
HAVE ALWAYS BEEN SUSPECT.

21:52.570 --> 21:54.606
INCLUDING THAT GUSTER.

21:54.640 --> 21:57.871
AND HIS SUPPOSEDLY
PSYCHIC FRIEND.

21:57.910 --> 21:59.468
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE US?

21:59.510 --> 22:01.842
YES, OF COURSE.

22:01.880 --> 22:03.848
YOU HAVE
TO FINISH PACKING YOUR WINE.

22:03.890 --> 22:06.848
YOU'RE MOVING INTO YOUR WINERY
IN NAPA ON FRIDAY,

22:06.890 --> 22:08.710
AND YOUR AMAZING COLLECTION
WILL FINALLY BE ON DISPLAY

22:08.760 --> 22:09.715
FOR ALL TO SEE.

22:09.760 --> 22:11.455
HEY, HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT--

22:11.490 --> 22:13.629
DON'T BE INTIMIDATED, SIR.

22:13.660 --> 22:14.922
I'M JUST A MAN.

22:20.740 --> 22:23.402
OH, GOD.
OH.

22:23.440 --> 22:24.600
(Shawn)
BRACE YOURSELF,

22:24.640 --> 22:26.528
JAN DOESN'T
ACTUALLY EXIST.

22:26.570 --> 22:27.673
WHAT?

22:27.710 --> 22:29.598
FACT, THERE IS NO RECORD
OF A JAN ANGLUND,

22:29.640 --> 22:31.699
BUYER OF FINE WINES AND FOOD
ON THE INTERNET ANYWHERE.

22:31.750 --> 22:33.547
I DID FIND A JEFF ANGLUND.

22:33.580 --> 22:36.708
HE'S AN ALBINO WITH A WEBSITE
DEDICATED TO SHORT CIRCUIT.

22:36.750 --> 22:38.149
YOU PUT US
ON THE EMAIL LIST?

22:38.190 --> 22:39.487
THAT'S A GIVEN.

22:39.520 --> 22:40.487
NICE.

22:40.520 --> 22:42.112
OH, SO SHE WAS LYING?

22:42.160 --> 22:44.788
OR SHE REALLY IS CHECKING
INTO THE NUTCRACKER SUITE.

22:44.830 --> 22:48.425
HEAR ME, MIRA MADE JAN UP.

22:48.460 --> 22:51.167
SHE MADE HIM UP?

22:51.200 --> 22:54.431
WHAT IS...

22:54.470 --> 22:55.459
CLOZAPINE?

22:55.500 --> 22:57.559
IT'S AN ANTI-ANXIETY DRUG.

22:57.610 --> 22:59.430
IT'S ALSO USED
TO TREAT PSYCHOSIS.

22:59.470 --> 23:00.607
BINGO.

23:00.640 --> 23:01.902
MIRA HAD A PRESCRIPTION
TO CLOZAPINE,

23:01.940 --> 23:03.476
BUT THE REFILL DATE WAS
FROM WAY BACK WHEN,

23:03.510 --> 23:05.171
AND SHE HAD A BUNCH
OF PILLS LEI-T.

23:05.210 --> 23:06.279
SO SHE WAS OFF HER MEDS.

23:06.310 --> 23:08.813
AND OFF HER ROCKER.
EVEN MORE SO THAN HER MOTHER.

23:08.850 --> 23:10.408
WHAT?

23:10.450 --> 23:11.986
LET'S JUST SAY I KNOW WHERE MIRA
GETS HER FREAKY SIDE.

23:12.020 --> 23:13.612
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

23:13.660 --> 23:16.811
I WAS FEELING BAD FOR MIRA.
I EVEN STARTED TO--

23:16.860 --> 23:19.624
OH, MY GOSH!

23:19.660 --> 23:21.799
SHAWN, SHE DID ALL THIS
TO GET ME BACK.

23:21.830 --> 23:22.819
I FELL FOR IT AGAIN.

23:22.860 --> 23:25.499
BUT WAIT, THERE'S MORE.

23:25.530 --> 23:26.724
THE PICTURES.

23:33.680 --> 23:35.033
I SENSE SOMETHING IS VERY,
VERY, VERY WRONG

23:35.080 --> 23:37.571
ABOUT THESE PHOTOS,
VERY WRONG INDEED.

23:37.610 --> 23:40.477
JAN ANGLUND DOESN'T EXIST.

23:42.550 --> 23:44.188
THANK YOU AND GOOD NIGHT.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT A MINUTE!

23:44.220 --> 23:46.211
JAN--JANN IS REAL.

23:46.250 --> 23:47.717
WHY WOULD I MAKE ANY OF THIS UP?

23:47.760 --> 23:49.648
TO TRICK ME
INTO FALLING FOR YOU AGAIN.

23:49.690 --> 23:50.554
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'D GO

23:50.590 --> 23:53.923
THROUGH ALL OF THIS
JUST TO GET ME BACK.

23:53.960 --> 23:55.120
HOW SURE ARE YOU
ABOUT THIS THEORY?

23:55.160 --> 23:57.526
CRYSTAL.

23:57.570 --> 24:00.164
THAT DOESN'T REALLY WORK.
VERY, VERY SURE.

24:00.200 --> 24:04.603
MM-HMM.
THEN HOW DO YOU EXPLAIN HIM?

24:04.640 --> 24:06.005
[Mira gasps]

24:06.040 --> 24:07.166
JANN!

24:07.210 --> 24:09.701
(Jann)
MIRA, HONEY, I'M SO SORRY.

24:12.710 --> 24:15.110
I'M GONNA GRAB A CLARK BAR
FROM THE VENDING MACHINE.

24:15.150 --> 24:17.584
UH, ANYONE ELSE WANT ANYTHING?
CHIEF?

24:17.620 --> 24:18.917
JULES?

24:18.950 --> 24:21.885
GUS, YOU'RE GOOD?
OKAY.

24:25.660 --> 24:27.082
OH, HONEY--I LOOKED FOR YOU
AT THE WINERY,

24:27.130 --> 24:28.097
BUT THEY SAID
YOU WERE HERE.

24:28.130 --> 24:30.496
WHERE WERE YOU?

24:30.530 --> 24:31.497
YOU DIDN'T GET MY MESSAGE?

24:31.530 --> 24:32.827
(Mira)
WHAT MESSAGE?

24:32.870 --> 24:34.497
(Jann)
AT THE HOTEL DESK.

24:34.540 --> 24:35.768
UH, LOOK, I GOT A CALL

24:35.800 --> 24:37.961
TO CLOSE THIS DEAL WITH THESE
VENTURE CAPITALISTS IN PORTUGAL.

24:38.010 --> 24:39.966
IT WAS
FOR A VERY IMPORTANT CLIENT,

24:40.010 --> 24:41.568
AND I THOUGHT I COULD GET BACK
IN TIME.

24:41.610 --> 24:43.601
[whispers]
VENTURE CAPITALISTS,
REALLY?

24:43.650 --> 24:44.947
I'M SO SORRY.
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE GONE.

24:44.980 --> 24:46.800
I MISSED OUR BIG DAY.

24:46.850 --> 24:48.545
(Mira)
I'M JUST GLAD YOU'RE OKAY.

24:48.580 --> 24:50.582
WHY DON'T WE TALK
ABOUT THIS BACK AT THE WINERY

24:50.620 --> 24:52.212
AND SPEND SOME TIME
GETTING TO KNOW YOU.

24:52.250 --> 24:55.651
YEAH.
JUST GIVE ME ONE SECOND.

24:59.860 --> 25:01.828
YOU...BOTH.

25:01.860 --> 25:03.691
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO SAY TO YOU.

25:03.730 --> 25:07.996
HOW COULD YOU BE SO CRUEL?

25:08.040 --> 25:11.806
DOESN'T EXIST, HUH?
THAT'S GREAT.

25:11.840 --> 25:13.808
HEY, SHOULD I PUT OUT
AN IMAGINARY A.P.B. FOR HIM

25:13.840 --> 25:15.273
ON MY INVISIBLE RADIO?

25:15.310 --> 25:16.800
I HAVE A CASE TO WORK.

25:16.840 --> 25:18.068
SO DO I.

25:22.580 --> 25:23.842
DAMN IT, SHAWN.

25:23.890 --> 25:25.915
YOU MADE ME LOOK LIKE A FOOL
IN FRONT OF MIRA.

25:25.950 --> 25:27.713
DUDE, YOU KNOW DEEP, DEEP DOWN

25:27.760 --> 25:29.785
THAT THERE IS SOMETHING WEIRD
GOING ON HERE.

25:29.820 --> 25:31.321
WITH MIRA.

25:31.360 --> 25:33.590
WITH JAN SUDDENLY APPEARING
OUT OF NOWHERE.

25:33.630 --> 25:34.892
I'M GONNA PROVE IT TO YOU.

25:34.930 --> 25:37.057
I'M GONNA SHOW YOU
THAT SOMETHING'S GOING ON.

25:37.100 --> 25:38.124
NO.
NO MORE, SHAWN.

25:38.170 --> 25:39.899
STOP IT.
I'M SERIOUS ABOUT THIS.

25:39.930 --> 25:41.238
FINE.

25:41.270 --> 25:43.864
FOR YOU, I'LL STOP.

25:43.910 --> 25:45.866
THANK YOU.

25:53.210 --> 25:54.814
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

25:54.850 --> 25:57.114
WELL, I WAS HOPING TO SPEAK
WITH JAN FOR A MINUTE.

25:57.150 --> 25:58.344
JANN.

25:58.390 --> 26:00.017
I WON'T CALL HIM THAT.

26:00.050 --> 26:03.110
YEAH, HE'S OFF PLAYING GOLF
WITH MY FATHER.

26:03.160 --> 26:04.354
AH, SWEET.

26:04.390 --> 26:07.052
IS THAT IT?
'CAUSE I'M BUSY.

26:07.090 --> 26:09.695
ACTUALLY, THERE IS
ONE MORE THING.

26:09.730 --> 26:12.028
JUST BETWEEN YOU AND ME,

26:12.070 --> 26:15.289
WHY'D YOU FAKE THOSE PICTURES
OF YOU AND JAN?

26:15.340 --> 26:16.932
I MAY HAVE BEEN WRONG
ABOUT A COUPLE OF THINGS,

26:16.970 --> 26:19.768
BUT I KNOW FOR A FACT
THAT THOSE PICTURES ARE FAKES.

26:19.810 --> 26:22.005
JAN HAD A SHAVING CUT
IN THE SAME PLACE ON HIS NECK

26:22.040 --> 26:23.701
IN EACH ONE OF THESE PICTURES

26:23.750 --> 26:25.968
EVEN THOUGH THEY WERE TAKEN
AT DIFFERENT TIMES OF THE YEAR.

26:26.010 --> 26:29.776
IT'S GUS' FAULT.

26:29.820 --> 26:30.718
REALLY.

26:30.750 --> 26:32.308
EVER SINCE WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN HE AND I,

26:32.350 --> 26:33.681
MY PARENTS HAVE BEEN SKEPTICAL

26:33.720 --> 26:36.154
OF EVERY GUY I'VE BEEN WITH.

26:36.190 --> 26:40.058
ANDY, AMIR, GURU ANUPAM,
GAY AN DY, ANTHONY...

26:40.090 --> 26:41.921
DOES GAY ANDY KNOW
YOU CALL HIM THAT?

26:41.960 --> 26:44.394
HE GAVE HIMSELF THAT NAME.

26:44.430 --> 26:45.988
LOOK, JANN AND I HAD ONLY BEEN
TOGETHER FOR A FEW WEEKS

26:46.030 --> 26:47.998
WHEN WE DECIDED TO GET MARRIED,
AND I KNOW THAT'S CRAZY,

26:48.040 --> 26:50.634
BUT I JUST BELIEVE
IN ALL OR NOTHING.

26:50.670 --> 26:52.001
YOU KNOW,
DOING WHAT FEELS RIGHT.

26:52.040 --> 26:53.007
ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME, SHAWN?

26:53.040 --> 26:53.938
WHAT,
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

26:53.980 --> 26:55.231
I SPENT AN ENTIRE SEASON

26:55.280 --> 26:57.077
WITH AN INTERPRETIVE DANCE GROUP
IN BUFFALO.

26:57.110 --> 26:58.748
BUT, SEE, MY PARENTS
WERE AGAINST THIS THING

26:58.780 --> 26:59.849
FROM THE WHOLE BEGINNING.

26:59.880 --> 27:01.211
SO JANN PHOTOSHOPPED
SOME PICTURES

27:01.250 --> 27:02.717
TO MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
WE HAD BEEN TOGETHER

27:02.750 --> 27:04.684
FOR LONGER THAN WE HAD,
AND IT WORKED.

27:04.720 --> 27:05.982
WAIT A SECOND.

27:06.020 --> 27:07.681
YOU'RE SAYING THE PICTURES
WERE JAN'S IDEA?

27:07.720 --> 27:09.688
NO, JANN.

27:09.720 --> 27:11.256
AND YEAH, HE'S THE ONE
WITH THE SUPER-FAST PRINTER.

27:11.290 --> 27:12.427
[phone rings]

27:12.460 --> 27:14.018
I GOTTA GET THAT.

27:14.060 --> 27:15.925
UH, THAT'S COMING
FROM THE ROOM NEXT DOOR.

27:15.960 --> 27:17.769
MIRA, MIRA, MIRA!

27:20.130 --> 27:21.961
I SAID I WAS SORRY
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED WITH MIRA.

27:22.000 --> 27:23.763
I AM TRYING TO MAKE IT UP
TO YOU HERE.

27:23.810 --> 27:24.936
COME ON, MAN,

27:24.970 --> 27:26.005
WE HAVEN'T PLAYED GOLF
IN FOREVER.

27:26.040 --> 27:27.837
THIS IS GONNA BE FUN.

27:27.880 --> 27:30.007
PLUS, I PROMISE TO KEEP
MY CADDYSHAC REFERENCES

27:30.040 --> 27:31.769
TO A MINIMUM.

27:34.480 --> 27:36.016
NOW, I'VE HEARD THIS CLUB
IS RESTRICTED,

27:36.050 --> 27:37.938
SO, UH, DON'T TELL 'EM
YOU'RE JEWISH.

27:37.990 --> 27:39.014
SHAWN.

27:39.050 --> 27:40.950
I DIDN'T SAY
I WOULDN'T MAKE ANY.

27:40.990 --> 27:44.050
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:44.090 --> 27:45.182
THE LADY'S TEE'S UP THERE.

27:59.010 --> 28:00.807
DUDE!

28:00.840 --> 28:01.807
YOU KNOW WHAT WOULD BE MORE FUN?

28:01.840 --> 28:03.068
STARTING
ON THE BACK NINE.

28:03.110 --> 28:05.169
WHY CAN'T WE JUST START
FROM HERE?

28:05.210 --> 28:09.078
I CAN PAR THIS HOLE
WITH THIS PUTT.

28:28.140 --> 28:29.892
YES, YES, YES.

28:29.940 --> 28:30.907
GREAT SHOT.
LET'S GO.

28:30.940 --> 28:32.066
SHAWN!

28:32.110 --> 28:33.168
SHAWN, GET BACK HERE

28:33.210 --> 28:36.202
BEFORE I ADD TWO STROKES
TO YOUR SCORE!

28:36.240 --> 28:37.468
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?
SHH!

28:37.510 --> 28:40.502
(Gus)
IS THIS THE REAL REASON
YOU BROUGHT ME GOLFING?

28:40.550 --> 28:42.370
TO FOLLOW JANN?
I TOLD YOU TO DROP IT.

28:42.420 --> 28:45.048
HE'S BACK.
THERE'S NO MORE CASE.

28:45.090 --> 28:47.513
DUDE, YOU'RE WRONG.
JAN IS THE CASE.

28:47.550 --> 28:48.517
HE'S THE KEY.

28:48.560 --> 28:51.950
YOU'RE LOSING IT.

28:51.990 --> 28:54.129
GUS. GUS!

28:57.230 --> 28:59.528
THAT'S THE P.I.
FROM THE BATTING CAGES.

28:59.570 --> 29:01.765
EVEN YOU HAVE TO ADMIT
THIS IS GETTING WEIRD.

29:04.110 --> 29:09.309
ACT NATURAL.

29:09.340 --> 29:11.205
(Jann)
HEY, WHAT ARE
YOU GUYS DOING HERE?

29:11.250 --> 29:13.104
WHAT'S UP?

29:13.150 --> 29:14.879
JUST PLAYING
A LITTLE GOLF.

29:14.920 --> 29:17.218
KEEPING AN EYE OUT
FOR SUSPICIOUS MEETINGS

29:17.250 --> 29:18.478
BETWEEN SHADY PEOPLE.

29:18.520 --> 29:20.511
WHAT WERE YOU AND MACE RHODEN
ARGUING ABOUT?

29:20.550 --> 29:22.108
[laughs]

29:22.160 --> 29:23.013
THAT WAS NOTHING.

29:23.060 --> 29:25.085
YOU KNOW, I WAS THE GUY
WHO HIRED HIM.

29:25.130 --> 29:28.019
I WAS LATE PAYING,
SO HE WAS KIND OF UPSET.

29:28.060 --> 29:30.358
MAYBE MIRA DIDN'T TELL YOU,
BUT I'M A PSYCHIC, YEAH.

29:30.400 --> 29:33.028
AND RIGHT NOW THE SPIRITS
ARE SCREAMING SOMETHING

29:33.070 --> 29:35.095
IN MY HEAD
OVER AND OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

29:35.140 --> 29:38.928
THEY'RE SAYING,
"SO SE PROMETER USAR AS PENAS."

29:38.970 --> 29:40.528
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:40.570 --> 29:43.277
IT'S PORTUGUESE FOR
"ONLY IF YOU PROMISE

29:43.310 --> 29:44.402
TO KEEP
YOUR FEATHERED HEADDRESS ON."

29:44.450 --> 29:47.078
HOW CAN YOU POSSIBLY
DO BUSINESS

29:47.110 --> 29:49.817
IN PORTUGAL AND NOT SPEAK
A WORD OF THE LANGUAGE?

29:49.850 --> 29:51.886
WHY DID YOU
REALLY MISS THE WEDDING?

29:51.920 --> 29:55.185
OKAY, I WASN'T IN EUROPE.

29:55.220 --> 29:56.187
YES!

29:56.220 --> 29:57.209
LOOK, THE TRUTH IS,

29:57.260 --> 29:59.228
I WAS IN ANOTHER RELATIONSHIP.

29:59.260 --> 30:00.522
I WAS IN A BAD SITUATION.

30:00.560 --> 30:02.494
I HAD TO END IT BEFORE I
COULD GET MARRIED TO MIRA.

30:02.530 --> 30:04.122
YOU WERE CHEATING ON MIRA?

30:04.170 --> 30:05.421
NO, ALL RIGHT?
NO.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.836
NOT EXACTLY, OKAY?
IT STARTED BEFORE WE EVEN MET.

30:07.870 --> 30:10.907
AND I PROMISE YOU,
IT'S OVER NOW.

30:10.940 --> 30:12.908
I KNOW THAT I HAVEN'T
ALWAYS BEEN A GOOD GUY.

30:12.940 --> 30:16.239
BUT BEING WITH MIRA,

30:16.280 --> 30:18.168
YOU KNOW,
IT'S CHANGED ME.

30:18.210 --> 30:20.178
I REALIZE NOW
THAT SHE'S THE ONLY THING

30:20.210 --> 30:21.347
IN MY LIFE THAT MATTERS.

30:21.380 --> 30:22.938
AND YOU MAY NOT BELIEVE ME,

30:22.980 --> 30:25.187
BUT THAT IS THE TRUEST THING
I HAVE EVER SAID.

30:25.220 --> 30:29.259
LOOK, I'D BETTER GET BACK
BEFORE MIRA'S DAD

30:29.290 --> 30:30.359
DESPISES ME EVEN MORE.

30:36.600 --> 30:38.465
SHAWN...

30:38.500 --> 30:40.866
I'VE BEEN THERE BEFORE
WHEN IT COMES TO MIRA.

30:40.900 --> 30:42.231
HE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

30:42.270 --> 30:45.159
YEAH,
BUT HE'S DEFINITELY LYING.

30:45.210 --> 30:47.064
HOW CAN HE BE DOING BOTH?

30:47.110 --> 30:48.270
TRUST ME.

30:48.310 --> 30:50.870
AS SOMEONE WHO HAS OCCASIONALLY
DEALT WITH HALF-TRUTHS,

30:50.910 --> 30:53.276
JAN BRADY IS NOT TELLING US
EVERYTHING.

30:53.310 --> 30:54.572
(Lassiter)
HE'S MY INFORMANT.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.349
I'LL GET
THE INFORMATION WE NEED.

30:56.380 --> 30:58.439
CARLTON,
THIS IS MY CASE.

30:58.490 --> 31:00.913
AND BESIDES, YOUR TOUGH-GUY
INTERROGATION TECHNIQUE,

31:00.960 --> 31:02.211
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

31:02.260 --> 31:03.249
OH, AND YOU THINK
SWEET AND GENTLE'S

31:03.290 --> 31:04.086
GONNA GET INFO
FROM A GUY LIKE THIS?

31:04.130 --> 31:06.280
PLEASE.
ALL I NEED IS 30 SECONDS.

31:06.330 --> 31:07.285
YOU COULD TIME ME.

31:07.330 --> 31:09.389
FINE, I'LL PLAY THAT GAME.

31:09.430 --> 31:10.397
AND I WILL BEAT YOU AT IT.

31:10.430 --> 31:12.022
FINE.
MCNAB!

31:12.070 --> 31:14.334
WE'RE COMMANDEERING
YOUR WATCH.

31:14.370 --> 31:15.268
YOU'RE COMMANDEERING MY--

31:15.300 --> 31:16.267
WATCH .

31:16.300 --> 31:18.939
OKAY.

31:21.510 --> 31:23.000
NOW WATCH...

31:23.040 --> 31:24.302
HOW I BREAK THIS GUY.

31:24.350 --> 31:26.102
IT'S ALL IN THE EYES.

31:30.420 --> 31:33.480
[stopwatch beeps]

31:48.470 --> 31:50.233
ALL RIGHT.

31:50.270 --> 31:51.237
YOU LITTLE SON OF A--

31:51.270 --> 31:52.237
TIME!

31:52.270 --> 31:53.532
WHAT?
I JUST GOT STARTED.

31:53.570 --> 31:54.969
THEY'RE YOUR RULES.

31:55.010 --> 31:56.329
CRAP.

32:00.510 --> 32:01.477
HEY.

32:01.520 --> 32:02.509
HI.

32:02.550 --> 32:04.347
YOU LOOK HUNGRY.

32:04.390 --> 32:06.119
KIN DA.

32:06.150 --> 32:08.015
THAN KS.

32:08.060 --> 32:10.187
SO...

32:10.220 --> 32:11.380
WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME

32:11.430 --> 32:12.954
ABOUT A REFRIGERATION TRUCK

32:12.990 --> 32:14.594
THAT WAS STOLEN A FEW DAYS AGO?

32:14.630 --> 32:17.292
REFRIGERATION TRUCK?

32:17.330 --> 32:21.369
OH, COME ON.
ALL I NEED'S A NAME, RUSTY.

32:21.400 --> 32:24.335
I KNOW ABOUT PRETTY MUCH
EVERY CAR BOOSTED

32:24.370 --> 32:26.634
IN SANTA BARBARA,

32:26.670 --> 32:28.171
BUT NOTHING AS POINTLESS

32:28.210 --> 32:29.279
AS STEALING
A REFRIGERATOR TRUCK.

32:29.310 --> 32:30.629
HONEST.

32:30.680 --> 32:32.272
[stopwatch beeps]

32:32.310 --> 32:33.379
TIME!

32:40.620 --> 32:42.679
ALL RIGHT,
CUT THE CRAP, RUSTY.

32:42.720 --> 32:44.688
WE BOTH KNOW
THAT YOU ARE HOLDING OUT ON ME.

32:44.730 --> 32:46.379
I WAS EATING
THAT CANDY BAR.

32:46.430 --> 32:48.295
WELL, THE CANDY POLICE
AREN'T HERE TODAY.

32:48.330 --> 32:49.558
IT'S JUST ME, AND I GOT
AT LEAST 12 DIFFERENT CHARGES

32:49.600 --> 32:51.067
I COULD PIN ON YOU.

32:51.100 --> 32:52.169
SO YOU BETTER START GIVING ME

32:52.200 --> 32:53.428
SOME GOOD INFORMATION.

32:53.470 --> 32:56.098
I DON'T KNOW.

32:56.140 --> 32:59.507
LOOK, THERE'S ONLY TWO REASONS
WHY ANYBODY STEALS A CAR.

32:59.540 --> 33:02.304
TO SELL IT OR TO USE IT.

33:02.340 --> 33:03.534
SINCE NOBODY'S COME DOWN
TO MY SHOP

33:03.580 --> 33:04.649
TO SELL ME
YOUR PRECIOUS LITTLE TRUCK,

33:04.680 --> 33:05.704
THEY NEED IT FOR SOMETHING.

33:05.750 --> 33:07.570
[stopwatch beeps]

33:07.610 --> 33:10.170
TIME!

33:10.220 --> 33:11.448
DON'T YOU DARE TELL HER A THING.

33:11.490 --> 33:13.685
OH, THAT'S GREAT
DETECTIVE WORK.

33:13.720 --> 33:16.086
PROBABLY WHY YOU SCORED A WHOLE
POINT LOWER THAN ME ON THE EXAM.

33:16.120 --> 33:17.087
SORRY TO INTERRUPT,

33:17.120 --> 33:18.678
BUT THE CHIEF NEEDS YOU
FOR AN IMPORTANT CASE.

33:24.200 --> 33:25.519
THEY TOOK
MY CLARK BAR.

33:25.570 --> 33:27.390
THEY TOOK MY WATCH.

33:32.470 --> 33:33.505
(Gus)
WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:33.540 --> 33:34.632
IT'S ABOUT MIRA'S FIANCE.

33:34.680 --> 33:38.104
I KNEW IT.
THE GUY'S A CROOK.

33:38.150 --> 33:40.471
ALL RIGHT!
PLAYTIME'S OVER, JAN!

33:40.510 --> 33:44.617
I'VE HAD A BAD PSYCHIC VIBE
ABOUT YOU FROM THE BEGINNING.

